Le-Lo-Du-87;-;After 2000 hours on this game, I believe I can made a correct review about it. Well, Team Fortress 2 is a free to play FPS. Unlike in some FPS, being a great killer is not always the key to sucess. Indeed, teamwork often beats singlework even if this singlework team is made of real good players. 9 differents classes with their pros and their cons. Some classes can be hard for beginners, for example spy. However, some are easy for them. A good point is that each class, even if it seems to be easy to play at first, can be really effective after some training. There are a lot of weapons,most of which are balanced (Some are not though). I would say there're many ways to waste your money with this game, but if you're clever enough, it's possible to have fun without spending too much money (Mainly to get the prenium pack, nothing more). The lastest update and Mann up need money to be played (Well, you can buy mann up tickets on market). Nevertheless, you can play a similar gamemode which is free, except rewards. Since it's a rather old game, there are a lot of custom gamemodes and maps which can enhance your gaming experience. The amount of maps and gamemodes is very high, which prevents you from getting bored in this game. Even after spending 2000 hours, I'm still having fun. Community however can be an annoyance. Some preniums players act very badly with beginners, and show off how they spend their money (You know, they think paying tons of money on a game will make you strong and skillfull, prff). On an other hand, there are some servers where you need to pay in order to win and Valve servers where teamwork is almost impossible since beginners think they're in a singlework game. A pro tip : Don't wear Gibus hat if you don't want to get mocked. In the end, I would like say that this game worth a try. You may not like it, but I rather think you'll enjoy it if you're a FPS and teamwork player. The game is kind of old, but is not dead yet (And the cartoon graphics ire ok). Also, be carefull of trading madness, some players and of excessive money spending.
