Soundpulse;-;Team Fortress 2 is the sequel to Team Fortress Classic. It was included in the Orange Box, along with Half-Life 2, Half-Life 2 Episode 1, Half-Life 2 Episode 2, and Portal. It was released in 2007, running on the Source Engine. It's a class-based FPS that relies on teamwork. For Offense, there is Scout, Soldier, and Pyro. Defense has Demoman, Heavy, and Engineer. Support has Medic, Sniper, and Spy. Pros: -The quite cartoony graphics make it unique. It brings a new feel to the Source Engine, and it does well. -There are no overpowered classes. Everything is balanced. Each class is made to counter each other. -Unlike TFC, there is music in the game. -Tons of gamemodes and maps, including custom ones. -The gameplay has improved since TFC. Airblast, Ubercharge, etc. -Constant updates. -Unlike TFC, there are extra weapons. Each weapon is made for certain situations. -Hats. Cons: -Music only plays during the title screen or class select screen. -The community can be pretty bad. The amount of naked pony sprays explain a lot. -Too many trade/achievement servers. -Updates never seem to be tested, and each bug fix brings at least 2 more bugs. 7.5/10
