Makise Kurisu;-;TF2 at it's core is an amazing game, and one of the most fun and balanced shooters I've ever played. Even though choices by Valve have tarnished it's reputation (and I mean they really screwed the pooch on more than one occasion), it still stands out as one of the most fun and addicting shooters there is. However, to get the full enjoyment out of it you either need to find a community server (which since Quickplay started defaulting only to Valve servers, is becoming harder) or play competitive. Valve's public servers have little to no team cohesion or coordination (owing to the Free-to-Play system bringing in LOTS of children). Don't worry if you get destroyed by more experienced players, you'll get better (trial by fire worked for me). If you need help, ask. You can't be an asset to your team if you have no clue what you're doing. Ask for tips from experienced players, and always remember that there is a wiki [wiki.teamfortress.com] . And for god's sake, use a ing mic. Don't have a mic? Get one, teamwork and communication is key. The game isn't what it used to be, you can't drop in to a random server and expect to find competent and friendly players anymore, the visually appealing and unique artstyle has been destroyed by cash-grab cosmetics, and the actual performance of the game has been destroyed by the added weight of the cosmetics. Still, even as frustrating as it can be, there's never anything more satisfying than coordinating a team through a difficult push to win a close victory. (Also, a final note. If the server you join has an MOTD, read it.)
