Magnesium Hydroxide;-;Warning: This game is most fun when you know your  at least half-way, and have some experience. It may be repelling at first. This is a incredibly fun and addictive FPS. The graphics are stylized in a cartoonish fashion, making this one of the most recognizable games. The maps are very well-designed which is something Valve always gives us. I guess some introduction to the gameplay would be nice, so here you go: The gameplay centers around 9 classes, each with a unique playstyle and different skills required to play this class efficiently. Every with their own weaknesses and strengths. Only full co-operation between the usually 12 players will bring victory to the team. You have to know your , or be called a noob. This can be solved by reading guides, completing tutorials and simply practicing on public servers. You need to get into the mood to play a class, which can easily be achieved by simply playing it for a while. Something important to note is that there is no campaign, but offline practice does exist. The community is incredibly active. Nothing more can be said. You can download custom models, sounds and even HUDs! Some people may say it's pay to win. This just isn't true. The items in the store are used only to earn respect and don't effect gameplay at all. While weapons are buyable, it's completely pointless to buy them there. You can get it randomly literally anytime, or by trading. I guarantee that if you go on a full 32-player trade server, someone will own the weapon you're looking for, and won't ask much for it at all. I have never had so much fun playing a multiplayer-based community-fueled game. P.S don't play as sniper. Snipers are cowards. P.P.S #CoDSucks
