The Flying Walrus|AFK 1 WEEK|;-;What is there to say about Tf2 that has not already been said? Not much really so I am going to try and keep this short. This game has some of the best class based mechanics that can be found in any FPS. Each class is different and provides a different style of play to have fun with, and that is just the stock characters. Customization is one of this games strong points, in what other game can I jump across a map with a pink beard and hat and then proceed to smash a shovel into a friends face causing them to endlessly rage? There is a reason that people still play this after 7 years. TF2 has taken many hours of my life, and I'm fine with that as longs as it continues to stay awesome I will spend many more hours in the future. "Arf"- Walruse
Krunchy Anarchy [AoG];-;I've been Playing Team Fortress since the beginning of this summer 2013, to be honest I haven't played a game that can matche up to Team Fortress, and no matter how boring you are the Fun Never ends, it keeps going, going and going.
Doctor Pockets;-;Introduction Team Fortress 2 has really surprised me. While It has no story or co-op modes, this has to be one of my favorites. Game play Simple multiplayer or bot matches, that's it. Campaign? Nah. There are some fun gamemode that include: arena, capture the flag, control point, king of the hill, mann vs. machine, payload, special delivery, territorial control, and even a dueling mini-game. What else can you ask for? Hats? Yes, Valve has added hundreds of hats for you which can cost hundreds of $$$. But why waste you hard-earned cash on a digital hat? You don't need to! Trading can get you 1 ordinary wepon to unusual hats, but with a cost. Not a money cost but lots lots lots of time. Away from that you can customize your loadouts and play 9 different classes. Scout Soldier Pyro Demoman Heavy Engineer Medic Sniper Spy Each has there own advantages and disadvantages that make the gameplay different for each class. Sniper litterally snipes you from the corner of the map and medic heals you. Playing each can get you to your favorite. In-game items that you get by random drops can complete change your style of play. Each wepon can either reload faster but shoot slower or completely opposite. There are custom maps and plugins that can change the game from shoot stuff and kill things to slender and even role playing. Sprays can be a problem if someone is watching you (people can relate) and players can rage on mic. Most people are friendly and some never stop playing this game. Graphics/other Cartoon-like characters and lots of gore. Lower-end PCs can also handle the game, but on lower settings. Good graphics, but you don't need better because its not realistic. Controls are normal, WASD to move, R to reload, MOUSE1 to shoot. Challenge level Easy bots can be a little difficult if it your first FPS or new to TF2. As you play more, expert goes from insta-killing you to easy. Real multiplayer can have noobs or MLG players. How fun it is Really fun. From walking into the super death trap of sentries or sticky jumping across them map, this game has been worth ever hour I played. Playing death run is great fun but Mario Kart can be better. There are many good laughs that I had while playing. Conclusion Play it.
