You gotta love his tenacity;-;Ah, Team Fortress 2... such a great game. If you don't listen to those people who complain about this game being to "cartoonish" then you will LOVE this game. I was invited by my friend, who said that this was a great game. At first, I thought it was alright, but I quit. However, since it's Free to play, you could imagine that I tried it once more, and i was officially hooked. So, whats so great about this game? It has a lot of fun and sometimes outright hilarious maps. Then, you have the classes. Being the guy who likes to get stuff done and over with fast, and the fact that I love fast characters in games, I LOVE the scout. Or maybe you like explosions. I would recommend the Soldier or Demoman. Want to be helpful to your team? Medic is the way to go! So many great options, and since there are only 9 classes, you would think that after figuring out how each class works, the game would get boring. Heheheheh... NOPE. There are a LOT of weapons other than the stock (starter, if you call it that.) weapons. There's the Black Box for soldier that gives you 15 health every hit... The Loch - N - Load (sorry if you don't like the spaces, it's just common for me to use them a lot.) in which you have to directly hit your enemy, but it does so much damage, and SO MUCH MORE WEAPONS. With a total of 27 "starter" weapons in the game, and even more weapons than just those that you can find, which are extremely fun to mess around with. Despite these things, a game sometimes messes up on a few things, which therefore makes the cons. One of the usual cons I see in multiplayer FPS games is that the community is bad, and I say so on this game. I'm not saying the community made maps or weapons are bad, which there pretty good, but some people who play this game just happen to be very rude. Don't get me wrong, I like most people who play this game, but everyone is going to run across either a troll spamming Rick Astley in the mic, or someone who is just rude. Usually, these people are probably in bad moods that day, but mostly not, they just want to either grab attention or be absolute trolls. Another con is that if your playing the game for the first time, your going to die. A LOT. This is usually the reason why some people quit TF2 so early. This isn't really a con, as it doesn't bother me that much, but one of my friends doesn't like this game because he isn't good at it. However, this game can get HILARIOUS. Such as: Backstabbing people and seeing them get sent over a building. Instant killing someone with a shovel while airborne. Watching people on spectator on the map sawmill run into the saws and killing themselves. it's what makes this a great game. If your alright with "cartoon - like graphics" and you like casual First Person Shooters, then please get this game right now. Speaking of now, excuse me as I go kill people with my scout...
