"YOU'RE FIRED!!!!!!";-;Ahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh, where to start with this game. This game is one of the best F2P FPS games out there and, frankly, one of the best games of all time. Pros: Can get every weapon withought having to pay. Awesome core gameplay. EXTREMELY ADDICTING. Awesome pace. Cons: If you are new, well.... get ready to get rekt.
TheGamingJedi (away 4 a week);-;TF2 is THE MOST popular free to play games in the history of free to play games. With over 220,000 reconsiderations it easily beats any other free to play games. I recommend playing this game as it offers a wide range of game play and keeps you entertained the whole game. Other than PvP game play there is a co-op mode which can be played for free or you can buy Tour Of Duty tickets and when you use those you can unlock rare and valuable items. There and 9 classes : 3 Support, 3 Defence and 3 Offence. First we have the Sniper, this is one of the classes you can relate to if you come from COD. It is a support class and once you find a good spot you become a living hell for the other team. Next we have the Spy, this class is known for its sneaky a attribute. This classes load out is ; A revolver, a butterfly knife, a sapper (to sap building from the engineer), a invis watch and a disguise kit so he can portray he's on the other team. His knife can back-stab and instantly kill any class from behind. Once you have got the hang of this class the other team would need to be cautious. Next we move on to the Pyro this is the Spys Nemesis, because if a pyro his a spy (disguised or invis) or any other class with its flame-thrower it will immediately catch fire, therefore showing the rest of the team that there is a spy. This fire causes after burn on any class this means that even after the pyro is dead the fire is dealing damage. Now we move on to the scout, the scout is the fastest class in the game and is made to deal damage and get out due to its low health. A scouts primary weapon is a scatter gun and when up close to enemy deals a large amount of damage. It 2nd weapon is a automatic pistol this weapon can be also seen as the engineers secondary. Its 3rd weapon is a metal bat this is used when you are up close to the enemy. Now we move onto the Engineer this calls is a defensive class and can build sentry guns, dispensers and teleporters. The buildings of the engineer either help team-mates out in a tough situation or help hold off a enemy attack. The buildings are vulnerable to spy Sappers, the sapper stops a building from working and also destroys the building after a period of time. Now we have the solider, this class consists of a rocket launcher, a shotgun and a shovel. This class is moderately effective in offence as it can kill most classes in 2 shots of his rocket launcher. Next we move on to the demo man, this class can be helpful in multiple situations its sticky-bomb launcher can be used to set traps for enemy pushes and its grenade launcher deals a very large amount of damage. This can be used as a very defensive class or offensive class. Now we move onto the medic, this class pretty much is self explanatory it heals other team mates... BUT we're talking about TF2 so nothing is that simple. After a majority of time of healing other players the medic will gain a power called UberCharge. The UberCharge can be used once to make 1 person on your team INVULNERABLE or about 7 seconds! When used with the heavy this is a VERY effective way of pushing the enemy backwards. Last but not least we have the Heavy, the face of valve the heavy's primary weapon is a mini gun! The mini gun deals a very large amount of damage output (the amount of damage gave off by a weapon). Combined with a medic a heavy become a VERY offensive class. When a medic has a UberCharge it would most likely charge the heavy as the heavy becomes a indestructible tank. This game has very balanced team game play and urges you to be a team player. I highly recommend this game.
