Illius[Accepting Case Donations];-;Silly Review? I tried quitting this game after hundreds of hours, turns out I just took a break. Serious review? It's an amazing FPS game with heavy emphasis on mobility and teamwork. There are various game modes, and 9 classes with strengths and weaknesses, meaning you HAVE to work together. You could do almost a chart that shows who trumps who (naturally speaking, any class can take any class if there is enough skill), such as Spy trumps Sniper trumps Pyro trumps Spy. Going back to mobility, if you pick this game up now I suggest heavily you learn mechanics of the game such as rocket jumping. Even as the slowest classes (Ex. Heavy) you never want to stop moving, meaning there is more skill than just "Shoot thing with gun". Along side this is the abundance of weapons and gamemodes, meaning that if you ever get a feeling the game is growing stale, just mix it up a bit and it's almost a whole new game. If all else fails, there are various user-made gamemodes (such as Vs Saxton Hale) to keep you entertained. And despite it's age, this game looks really good and each character has amazing personality, giving a great sense in charm (Something that lacks in the majority of FPS games...). Consider the age of this game and that it's still a heavily played game, you can see that it's worth playing. In terms of issues though there are some problems, such as some slightly unbalanced weapons (though this makes up a minority of them). This game is also at this point largely player-made as well; the majority of servers aren't even owned by Valve, and most added content are supplied by players. Overall: Great game, worth playing (And getting addicted to), but do NOT expect your everday shooter.
